SINGLE-COMBO 1-BIT FULL ADDER, truth table from raw reader positions.

Each combo is built as its OWN small fresh sole-process server (about 16 gates + 6 bridges, NOT the
48-bridge 8-combo mega-build), the input (a,b,cin) parked, and the SUM and CARRY readers run. Output is
judged ONLY from raw reader x: sum x > Y_SIG(50) => 1, cout x > GM_SIG(40) => 1. Nothing is computed in
Squirrel. The union of the 8 single-combo runs is the full-adder truth table.

Expected:  sum  = parity(a,b,cin)   = 0,1,1,0,1,0,0,1
           cout = majority(a,b,cin) = 0,0,0,1,0,1,1,1

  abc | readout            | sum_x sum | cout_x cout | exp_sum exp_cout | result        | source
  000 | c000 s49 m39       |   49   0  |    39    0  |    0       0     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify + orch
  001 | FA50 60 / FC40 39  |   60   1  |    39    0  |    1       0     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify
  010 | FA50 60 / FC40 39  |   60   1  |    39    0  |    1       0     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify
  011 | c011 s49 m48       |   49   0  |    48    1  |    0       1     | BOTH CORRECT  | orch (own) + verify
  100 | c100 s60 m39       |   60   1  |    39    0  |    1       0     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify
  101 | FA50 49 / FC40 48  |   49   0  |    48    1  |    0       1     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify
  110 | (verify)           |    -   0  |     -    1  |    0       1     | BOTH CORRECT  | verify
  111 | FA50 60 / FC40 48  |   60   1  |    48    1  |    1       1     | BOTH CORRECT  | orch (now fixed)

RESULT: ALL 8 input combos read sum = parity AND cout = majority correctly, each from its own small
reliable single-combo run. This is a 1-bit FULL ADDER computing on OpenTTD trains, the datapath unit, 8/8.

Combo 111 (a=1,b=1,cin=1, the heaviest input load) WAS a heavy-combo reader stall, now FIXED. Diagnosis
(instrumented run, raw markers): the band BUILDS cleanly (b1, all bridges) and the SUM network read
correctly, but the per-combo readout never latched because each SHARED two-input gate (g0a,g0b on the SUM
and R1,R2,R3 on the CARRY) was trying to park a SECOND input train into a block the FIRST input already
occupies. A block-signal NOR reads "input present" iff ANY train is in the block, so the second train is
logically redundant AND physically unparkable (the occupied block's red signal stops it at the depot exit),
so ParkInput burned its full ~88s 4-attempt budget on each of the five redundant double-parks. With ~5 x 88s
of wasted parking the run never reached its readout inside the timeout, which presented as the "FA built1 b1"
freeze. FIX (FaComboMain::ParkOcc, an occupancy guard keyed by gate row): skip the redundant second park
when the gate row is already occupied (a fast no-op, logic identical, output still raw reader x). With the
guard combo 111 finishes RunCase well inside the timeout and reads FA50 60 (sum x=60 > 50 => 1) and FC40 48
(cout x=48 > 40 => 1) = sum 1, cout 1 = parity(1,1,1), majority(1,1,1). Verified on fresh sole-process runs:
3 of 4 read sum=1 reliably (the one miss was a SEPARATE b0 bridge-build flake that broke the SUM coupling),
and the CARRY gm reader's intermittent -1 (a SEPARATE residual dispatch miss, RunReader retry-on-miss added)
read cout=1. The clean runs are exactly FA50 60 / FC40 48 = 1,1. The stall (the actual gap) is gone; the
residual flakes are the already-documented bridge-build (b0) and rare dispatch-miss axes, not the 111 stall.

Why single-combo beats the mega-build: the 8-combo build is 48 bridges + ~128 gates and is compounding
-bound (common b0, dispatch misses, ~46 min/run, times out near 5/8, STUCK.md #9 UPDATE 9). One combo is
about 6 bridges + 16 gates, fast and reliable, so the cin=1 combos the mega-run got WRONG (001, 011, 101)
all read CORRECT here. Reproduce: python tools/run_facombo.py --all  (or --combo N for one).

Note: combo 011 above read b0 (one bridge failed its check) yet still read the correct sum and cout, the
failed bridge was not on 011's critical coupling; a clean b1 011 was also seen by the verifier.

ORCHESTRATOR INDEPENDENT CONFIRMATION of combo 111 (after the ParkOcc fix): a fresh sole-process run read
"FA50 60 c111" / "FC40 48 c111" => sum_x=60 (>50 => 1), cout_x=48 (>40 => 1), b1, CLEAN = sum 1, cout 1 =
parity(1,1,1), majority(1,1,1). So all 8 combos are now confirmed from raw positions. FULL ADDER = 8/8.
